   <div class="row product">
      <div class="col-6  col-sm-5 col-md-4 col-lg-3 imageWrap">
         <div class="image"><a href="/Product/West-Ham-United-Football-Headlines---The-Telegraph-Custom-Gift-Book/29793409"><img src="/Content/StoreFront/assets/images/West ham angled front cover.jpg" /></a></div>
      </div>
      <div class="col-6 col-sm-7 col-md-8 col-lg-9 textWrap">
      <div class="productData"><h3><a href="/Product/West-Ham-United-Football-Headlines---The-Telegraph-Custom-Gift-Book/29793409">West Ham United Football Headlines - The Telegraph Custom Gift Book</a></h3><h5></h5>
          
          
      </div>
      <div class="purchase">
         
         <p class="price">£70.00</p>
         <div class="buttonWrap">
			 
			 <a class="button btn " href="/Product/West-Ham-United-Football-Headlines---The-Telegraph-Custom-Gift-Book/29793409">Read more</a>
		  </div>
		  

      </div>
      	  <div class="blurb"><p>When Jarrod Bowen’s late goal clinched victory for West Ham United over Fiorentina in the 2023 Europa Conference League final in Prague, it ended the club’s 43-year wait for a major honour. This Telegraph Custom Gift Book features match reports, articles and iconic images from the archives that chronicle the history of a club whose rare glory nights have been both memorable and merited – and whose influence extends beyond London’s East End.</p>
<p>Their impact was felt in the 1950s, when captain Malcolm Allison’s focus on coaching young players such as Bobby Moore effectively established one of the game’s first academies. The 1960s brought historic Wembley triumphs in the FA Cup in 1964, the Cup-Winners’ Cup in 1965 and, you could say, England’s World Cup win in 1966, when Moore captained the team and Geoff Hurst and Martin Peters scored all four goals in the final against West Germany.</p>
<p>FA Cup winners again in 1975 and 1980 – the latter remains the last time a second-tier club lifted the trophy – West Ham have retained their local identity while the English game has gone global. Youngsters still roll off the production line and attractive football remains part of the club’s DNA, if not of all those who have managed it. The move from the atmospheric Upton Park to the cavernous London Stadium in 2016 was seen by many as the end of an era, but four top-10 finishes and that night in Prague suggests otherwise. </p>
<p>Each book has a dark green leatherette cover with the recipient’s name embossed in silver.</p>
<p><i><b>Disclaimer</b><br>
This book is currently available on pre-order with an expected release date of April 30, 2024. We reserve the right to adjust this date if necessary. This book cannot be ordered in conjunction with another custom book. *Production is ongoing to capture recent media coverage for the book. Images used are for illustrative purposes only and may not reflect the final cover design.</p></i>
<p><b>Product specifications</b><br />
Made in the UK<br />
Size: A3 (29.7 x 42 cm)<br />
Colour: Dark green<br />
Embossing: Silver<br />
Material: Leatherette<br />
Care instructions: Dust gently with a dry cloth.</p>
